color:black">However, those fixes do not work for me. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:inherit;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:black">I am running on an&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:inherit;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:black">- i5 sandy bridge under Ubuntu 10.10 &nbsp;8 G RAM<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:inherit;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:black">- Kernel 2.6.32.14 with OpenVZ tweaks<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:inherit;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:black">- OpenMPI V 1.4.1</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:inherit;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:black">I am trying to migrate existing software to a new cluster (A,B)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Symptoms:</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">I can run the ring demo on a single machine, either A or B
with any number of processes.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">But when I combine the 2 machines I am limited to 2 processes,
any more and MPI hangs.&nbsp; &nbsp;It gets as far as:</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Process 0 sending 10 to 1, tag 201 (3 processes in ring)</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Process 0 sent to 1</p><p class="MsoNormal">and there it stays...</p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Any help greatly appreciated.</p>

